00:04:54.085 --> 00:04:55.754 position:50% align:center
[ERIKA]
Mm? Something wrong?

00:04:55.837 --> 00:04:58.506 position:50% align:center
[RIONA gasps]
Uh. It's nothing!

00:05:20.862 --> 00:05:22.530 position:50% align:center
Crap. I'm sorry.

00:05:22.614 --> 00:05:24.282 position:50% align:center
Don't worry about it.

00:05:24.366 --> 00:05:27.035 position:50% align:center
Let's take it easy at first
and get a good rally going.

00:05:27.118 --> 00:05:28.244 position:50% align:center
We can take our time
getting used to

00:05:28.328 --> 00:05:30.163 position:50% align:center
the ball going back and forth.

00:05:30.246 --> 00:05:31.373 position:50% align:center
Okay.

00:05:32.624 --> 00:05:34.417 position:50% align:center
Just one problem.

00:05:35.418 --> 00:05:36.878 position:50% align:center
[BADMINTON CLUB MEMBER 10A]
One point!

00:05:36.961 --> 00:05:38.296 position:50% align:center
[AYUMI]
Hm...

00:05:41.257 --> 00:05:44.260 position:50% align:center
We ain't got near enough people.

00:05:44.344 --> 00:05:46.638 position:50% align:center
But if no students
show up to practice,

00:05:46.721 --> 00:05:48.348 position:50% align:center
shouldn't that help in
the sense that it gives us

00:05:48.431 --> 00:05:50.892 position:50% align:center
a higher statistical chance
of winning on game day?

00:05:50.975 --> 00:05:52.519 position:50% align:center
Let's beat 'em
to a pulp, dangit!

00:05:52.602 --> 00:05:54.688 position:50% align:center
Yeah.

00:05:54.771 --> 00:05:57.524 position:50% align:center
[AYUMI] I'll show 'em what a
table tennis club member's got!

00:05:59.651 --> 00:06:00.652 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI]
Is this it?

00:06:00.735 --> 00:06:02.153 position:50% align:center
[YASUKO]
Over there, I think.

00:06:03.697 --> 00:06:07.075 position:50% align:center
Hey! Oh, is something wrong?

00:06:09.202 --> 00:06:11.496 position:50% align:center
Akebi!

00:06:11.579 --> 00:06:13.665 position:50% align:center
[AYUMI]
Um, what're y'all doin' here?

00:06:13.748 --> 00:06:16.001 position:50% align:center
Here we go!

00:06:16.084 --> 00:06:19.045 position:50% align:center
Ready, and... Fight on!

00:06:19.129 --> 00:06:21.506 position:50% align:center
Fight on! Table tennis!

00:06:21.589 --> 00:06:24.551 position:50% align:center
Fight on! Fight on!
Table tennis!

00:06:24.634 --> 00:06:27.846 position:50% align:center
Fight on! Fight on!
Table tennis!

00:06:27.929 --> 00:06:30.598 position:50% align:center
Fight on! Fight on!
Practice hard!

00:06:30.682 --> 00:06:32.726 position:50% align:center
[AYUMI]
Hey, tone it down!

00:06:33.727 --> 00:06:35.478 position:50% align:center
[MINORU]
What in the world was that?

00:06:35.562 --> 00:06:40.025 position:50% align:center
Wait, what do you mean?
It was a cheer!

00:06:40.108 --> 00:06:41.776 position:50% align:center
Seriously?

00:06:41.860 --> 00:06:43.278 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI]
Mm-hm!

00:06:43.361 --> 00:06:46.531 position:50% align:center
[KEI] I guess, we weren't
really very together, though.

00:06:46.614 --> 00:06:48.491 position:50% align:center
Yeah, how do you cheer, anyway?

00:06:48.575 --> 00:06:49.743 position:50% align:center
[KOMICHI]
Huh?

00:06:50.827 --> 00:06:51.786 position:50% align:center
Huh?

00:06:51.870 --> 00:06:53.038 position:50% align:center
Good question.

00:06:53.121 --> 00:06:56.166 position:50% align:center
When I think of it,
I guess what I imagine

00:06:56.249 --> 00:06:59.169 position:50% align:center
are the cheerleaders
in American TV shows.

00:06:59.252 --> 00:07:02.172 position:50% align:center
They hop and jump around
and do big lifts!

00:07:02.255 --> 00:07:03.631 position:50% align:center
Lifts?

00:07:04.924 --> 00:07:06.801 position:50% align:center
Fight on! Fight on!

00:07:06.885 --> 00:07:09.054 position:50% align:center
Fight on! Fight on!

00:07:09.137 --> 00:07:10.096 position:50% align:center
So cool!

00:07:10.180 --> 00:07:11.598 position:50% align:center
It means lifting
another cheerleader

00:07:11.681 --> 00:07:13.183 position:50% align:center
over your head.

00:07:13.266 --> 00:07:15.352 position:50% align:center
Of course! I've done that!

00:07:17.020 --> 00:07:18.438 position:50% align:center
Okay!

00:07:18.521 --> 00:07:22.734 position:50% align:center
[AYUMI]
Whoa! Whoa! Whoa! Stop, stop!

00:07:22.817 --> 00:07:25.945 position:50% align:center
